\begin_layout Standard
So he was sure that when he stepped on the glistening white road, hard and
 unyielding, though soft to the touch, almost like metal but more like porcelain
 or clay, he was indeed walking on the marble road.
 And that when he got off the marble road in search of a place to sleep
 awhile and rest before following it once more, it would still be there,
 an undisturbed reality, a known quantity, a fact.
 By the Gods, it was a 
