\begin_layout Standard
He could not know for certain, but though indeed impressive, the obelisk
 did not seem monumental, indeed awe inspiring.
 It felt more like a building, or a post, something long abandoned even
 though it was in perfect shape apparently.
 It did not seem as it had been erected, but rather like it had always been
 there, heedless of the sandy winds and scorching heat.
 The Pilgrim had stood aghast when he saw it, and in reverent tones started
 reciting from memory, his only source of knowledge:
