 an unnerving lack of sound.
 It had been done with a simple touch of the Pilgrim, as if he had been
 here many times before and quite intimately the workings of such a thing.
 When questioned about that, the Pilgrim had merely shrugged and said to
 Molo, 'God always provides'.
