Esphalon came to his mind, since he had mentioned divine providence as well.
 Was it a common theme? Was the desert and its extreme environment the one
 to blame for the changes he was going through? Was it a trick of perception,
 a misstep of the mind? Was it simply a coping mechanism? The array of questions
 that seemed to come unbidden to his weary mind suddenly became overwhelming.
 He had to give pause, rest, clear his mind, and then search within and
 without to find his answers.
 Maybe, as the Pilgrim had told him, the burden lay on him.
 It was time he had some sleep then.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
